Denis Law, Frank McLintock, Ian St John, Bertie Auld and John Robertson were among other Scottish icons nodding in accord.

From way south of the border came these Spurs celebrants of 80 years lived with uncompromising gallantry on the pitch and uncommon courtesy off it – Pat Jennings, Cliff Jones, Terry Medwin, Alan Mullery, Alan Gilzean, Steve Perryman, Mike England, Clive Allen.

Pick a team from those two glittering histories.

But when so doing reflect on something else spoken by Ferguson: ‘They talk about his great courage but he was a fantastic, skilful footballer whose intensity and desire to win would make any team.’

And keep a place for Dave Mackay.

